# Global Agent Instructions

This file is loaded by Gemini CLI at the start of every session, across all projects.
Project-specific instructions live in each repo's `GEMINI.md` (symlink to `AGENTS.md`).

## Communication Style

- Responses should be short and direct. No preamble, no trailing summaries.
- No emojis unless explicitly requested.
- When referencing code, include `file:line` so I can navigate directly.
- Default to no comments in code. Only add one when the WHY is non-obvious.

## General Rules

- Never commit or push without explicit instruction.
- Never modify `.envrc`, `.gitignore`, lock files, or CI workflows without explicit per-file approval.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Do not add error handling, fallbacks, or abstractions beyond what the task requires.
- When uncertain about scope, ask — don't infer approval from a broader instruction.

## Environment

- Shell: fish
- Package manager preference: uv (Python), npm (Node)
- Branch convention: `YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS` timestamped branches; never commit directly to main.
